We talk to industry experts in the mining sector about their current  R&D programmes and how new technology will drive their businesses in the future. Why should you be investing in research and development (R&D)? Proven sales growth Businesses that use research and development  investment as the catalyst for growth are more likely to achieve better results for shareholders. Competitive advantage Businesses are better positioned to compete in the worldwide marketplace with constant research and development  investments at the proper levels. Innovation Research and development results in highly valued inventions, ideas and designs that can be a source of value. Mission and ethos R&D is a necessary step toward furthering your company’s vision and goals. Thomas Holtz, CEO at Multotec, unpacks the company’s prototype technologies that will lead minerals processing into the future HERE